Many of these expenditures are unnecessary within city limits, leading to an inflated state budget. Last night on TV, I saw AG&G teaching children how to ice fish. Couldn't the parents take on that role? I pay property taxes, and I believe city residents would become more responsible stewards of resources if we were not reliant on state funds. For instance, office tenants could rent only the space they need, and the office rental market could self-regulate. In my previous business, I would ask my managers, "how do we reduce expenses?"
